  "text": "Bacteria and plasmids used in this study are listed in Table 1 . The parental strain for the knockout mutant was V. anguillarum VIB15, an O1 serotype strain which was originally isolated from a diseased sea bass in Greece [CITATION_1] . This strain was made rifampicin resistant (VIB15Rif   R   ) by natural selection, allowing survival of the bacterium in the gnotobiotic system used in this study. V. anguilllarum was grown in tryptic soy broth (TSB) (Oxoid, Erembodegem, Belgium) supplemented with 1% NaCl, or in marine broth (MB) (Difco Laboratories, Detroit, USA) for 24 hours at 28˚C. Escherichia coli strains were grown overnight in Luria Bertani (LB) broth or TSB at 37˚C. For solid media, 15 g/l of agar was added. Medium additives were used in the following concentrations when required: 40 mg/ml X-Gal (Invitrogen, Merelbeke, Belgium), 100 µg/ml ampicillin (Ap), 5 µg/ml chloramphenicol (Cm), 10 µg/ml, 100 µg/ml or 200 µg/ml rifampicin (Rif), and 50 µg/ml streptomycin (Sm) (Sigma Aldrich).",
